    <div class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h2 style="font-family:'Gill Sans', 'Gill Sans MT', Calibri, 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;color: #D17B88;">Introduction &#127804</h2>
            <p>When asked about their accommodation status people usually start complaining regardless of where they live. When the same question was asked to the female residents of the hostel,  participants exhibited a <B>consistent pattern of dissatisfaction</B>, particularly regarding hostel conditions.</p>

                <p>This led us to two main points:</p>
                <ol><li>There are some potential issues within hostel environments, indicating areas for improvement.</li>
                    <li>Certain external factors appeared to hinder residents from seeking alternative accommodation options</li></ol>
                <p>Our project aims to <b>comprehensively study residential preferences and challenges among students near the DTU campus</B>. With a focus on identifying hostel issues, understanding external influences on accommodation choices, and proposing improvements to enhance residential experiences we started our project by surveying the residents and exploring various living options around the DTU campus.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h2 style="font-family:'Gill Sans', 'Gill Sans MT', Calibri, 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;color: #D17B88;">Problem Statement &#128269</h2>
            <p><i><b>Finding out the potential issues in the girls’ hostel and the factors contributing to the participant’s continued preference for girls' hostels over PG and other accommodations</b></i></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content">
            <h2 style="font-family:'Gill Sans', 'Gill Sans MT', Calibri, 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;color: #D17B88;">Research Method &#128466</h2>
            <p>We mainly used <b>two methods</b> for research and data collection. To start off we surveyed a <b>sample size of 23</b> students consisting of hostel and outside campus female residents. The survey consisted of questions focused on their preferences and considerations when looking at various accommodations.
                We further conducted a <b>focus group with 6 people</b> to have an open discussion on the problems faced by the residents and what they want to change about their current situation.</p>
